        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>1</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008A/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>008A</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/008A/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Flow Matching For Generative Modeling">Flow Matching For Generative Modeling</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>These are notes on <fr:link href="/lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023/" title="Flow Matching for Generative Modeling" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023/" display-uri="lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023" type="local">Flow Matching for Generative Modeling</fr:link> prior to my group presentation on <fr:link href="/farebrotherTemporalDifferenceFlows2025/" title="Temporal Difference Flows" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/farebrotherTemporalDifferenceFlows2025/" display-uri="farebrotherTemporalDifferenceFlows2025" type="local">Temporal Difference Flows</fr:link> but can also be counted as a <fr:link href="/005G/" title="Papers of a Week" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/005G/" display-uri="005G" type="local"><![CDATA[#POTW]]></fr:link>.</html:p>
 <html:div class="jms-indent-block" style="
  margin-left: 1em;
  margin-bottom: 1em;
  border-left: 4px solid black;
  padding-left: 12px;
  background-color: whitesmoke;
  ">
  vs. <fr:link href="/007T/" title="Diffusion Models" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/007T/" display-uri="007T" type="local">Diffusion</fr:link>
  <html:ul><html:li><html:em>"We find that using FM provides more robust and stable training, and achieves superior performance compared to score matching."</html:em></html:li> 
   <html:li><html:em>"Furthermore, we find that our models produce better trade-offs between computational cost and sample quality."</html:em></html:li></html:ul>
 </html:div>
<fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008B</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008B/</fr:route><fr:title text="Probablity density path">Probablity density path</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>The <html:em>probability density path</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p: [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}_{>0}]]></fr:tex> is a time dependent probability density function i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\int  p_t(x)\mathrm {d}x = 1]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008C</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008C/</fr:route><fr:title text="Time-dependent vector field">Time-dependent vector field</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>We define a <html:em>time-dependent vector field</html:em> as a map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v: [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008D/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008D</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008D/</fr:route><fr:title text="Flow">Flow</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Give a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t]]></fr:tex> one can construct a time-dependent diffeomorphic map called a <html:em>flow</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi : [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex> defined via the ordinary differential equation
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {align*}
  \frac {\mathrm {d}}{\mathrm {d}t} \phi _t(x) &= v_t(\phi _t(x)) \\
  \phi _{0}(x) &= x
.\end {align*}]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
   Modeling a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> via a neural network i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t(x; \theta )]]></fr:tex> implicitly defines a deep parametric model of the flow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi _t(x)]]></fr:tex> via solving the ODE or an approximation, such as
   <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\phi _{t + \Delta  t}(x) \approx  \phi _t(x) + \Delta  t \cdot  v_t(\phi _t(x); \theta )]]></fr:tex>
   Obviously, accuracy will be dependent on the step size <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  t]]></fr:tex>.
 </fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
<fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008E/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008E</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008E/</fr:route><fr:title text="Generated probability paths">Generated probability paths</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>We say that a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> <html:em>generates</html:em> a <fr:link href="/008B/" title="Probablity density path" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/" display-uri="008B" type="local">probability density path</fr:link> if the <fr:link href="/008D/" title="Flow" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008D/" display-uri="008D" type="local">flow</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t]]></fr:tex> satisfies
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p_t = [\phi _t]_* p_{0},]]></fr:tex>
where
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[[\phi _t]_*p_{0}(x) = p_{0}(\phi _t^{-1}(x)) \det \left [ \frac {\partial  \phi _t^{-1} }{\partial  x}(x) \right ].  ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
A <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> generates a <fr:link href="/008B/" title="Probablity density path" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/" display-uri="008B" type="local">probability density path</fr:link> if it satisfies the continuity equation.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><html:p><html:strong>Quick notes (refine later)</html:strong>:
 Given data distribution <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q(x)]]></fr:tex>, we define an approximation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> with the form 
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p(x) = \int  p(x \mid  x_1) q(x_1) \mathrm {d}x_{1}]]></fr:tex>
In order to ensure <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x) \approx  q(x)]]></fr:tex>, we pick <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x \mid  x_{1})]]></fr:tex> that concentrates around <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_{1}]]></fr:tex> i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x \mid  x_{1}) \sim  N(x \mid  x_{1}, \sigma ^2 I)]]></fr:tex> for small <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>. If we then define the <html:em>conditional vector field</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t(\cdot  \mid  x_{1})]]></fr:tex> as the <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> that <fr:link href="/008E/" title="Generated probability paths" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008E/" display-uri="008E" type="local">generates</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x \mid  x_{1})]]></fr:tex> then define the <html:em>marginal vector field</html:em> as
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[v_t(x) = \int  v_t(x \mid  x_1) \frac {p(x \mid  x_1) q(x_{1})}{p(t)}]]></fr:tex>
then the <html:em>marginal vector field</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t]]></fr:tex> generates <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_t]]></fr:tex>, where we recall that
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p_t(x) = \int  p_t(x \mid  x_1) q(x_{1})]]></fr:tex>
which is supposedly a "good" approximation of the data distribution <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex>. We can then show that a <html:em>conditional flow matching loss</html:em> has the same gradient as the full <html:em>flow matching loss</html:em> i.e. our vector field should converge to the <html:em>marginal vector field</html:em>, which is a good approximation for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex>.
 </html:p><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>2</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008F/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008F</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008F/</fr:route><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>2</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008G/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008G</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008G/</fr:route><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>2</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008H/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008H</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008H/</fr:route><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>2</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008I/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008I</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008I/</fr:route><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter>
